In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in the Eastern Cape. “Regrettably, we report 53 more COVID-19 related deaths: Eastern Cape 17, Free State 11, Gauteng 8, Kwa-Zulu Natal 3, Limpopo 0, Mpumalanga 1, North West 0, Northern Cape 9 and Western Cape 4,” says Dr Mkhize. Recoveries stand at 1 495 864. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 10 413 180. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 569 935 the total number of deaths is 53 940 the total number of recoveries is 1 495 864. pic.twitter.com/mfcQIfhPB8 — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) April 21, 2021 